So, here's few basic component that's used within Vue.



v-on = Basically listening to DOM events (click, mouseover, mouseout) directly. You can set this into the template HTML.. For example:
v-bind = Binding a dynamic ID / Class.

// v-on //

<script setup>
import { ref } from 'vue'

const count = ref(0)

function increment() {
count.value++
}
</script>

<template>
<button v-on:click="increment"> Count is: {{ count }} </button>
</template>

// v-bind // 

<script setup>
import { ref } from 'vue'

const titleClass = ref('title')



</script>


<template>
<h1 v-bind:class="titleClass">Hello</h1>
</template>

<style>
.title {
color: red;
}
</style>
